"First root: %s\n"
"Second root: %s"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/globals.ml:161
msgid "path to synchronize"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/globals.ml:162
msgid ""
"When no \\verb|path| preference is given, Unison will simply synchronize the "
"two entire replicas, beginning from the given pair of roots.  If one or more "
"\\verb|path| preferences are given, then Unison will synchronize only these "
"paths and their children.  (This is useful for doing a fast sync of just one "
"directory, for example.)  Note that {\\tt path} preferences are interpreted "
"literally---they are not regular expressions."
msgstr ""

