"Protocol error: message data too big. This may be a bug or it\n"
"may be that your replicas are huge and the amount of updates\n"
"can't be handled by the current protocol implementation. If you\n"
"believe it is a bug then please consider reporting it.\n"
"Otherwise, try reducing the amount of updates by syncing the\n"
"replicas in smaller steps (using the \"path\" preference, for\n"
"example). You may have to do this for the initial sync only."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/remote.ml:801
msgid "path to the ssh executable"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/remote.ml:802
msgid ""
"This preference can be used to explicitly set the name of the ssh executable "
"(e.g., giving a full path name), if necessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/remote.ml:808
msgid "other arguments (if any) for remote shell command"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/remote.ml:809
msgid ""
"The string value of this preference will be passed as additional arguments "
"(besides the host name and the name of the Unison executable on the remote "
"system) to the \\verb|ssh| command used to invoke the remote server. The "
"backslash is an escape character."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/remote.ml:823
msgid "name of unison executable on remote server"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/remote.ml:824
msgid ""
"This preference can be used to explicitly set the name of the Unison "
"executable on the remote server (e.g., giving a full path name), if "
"necessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/remote.ml:831
msgid "add version number to name of unison on server"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/remote.ml:832
msgid ""
"When this flag is set to {\\tt true}, Unison will use \\texttt{unison-"
"\\ARG{currentmajorversionnumber}} instead of just \\verb|unison| as the "
"remote server command (note that the minor version number is dropped -- "
"e.g., unison-2.51).  This allows multiple binaries for different versions of "
"unison to coexist conveniently on the same server: whichever version is run "
"on the client, the same version will be selected on the server."
msgstr ""

#: ../src/remote.ml:1179
msgid "use a streaming protocol for transferring file contents"
msgstr ""

#: ../src/remote.ml:1180
msgid ""
"When this preference is set, Unison will use an experimental streaming "
"protocol for transferring file contents more efficiently. The default value "
"is \\texttt{true}."
msgstr ""

